description: Request for Standing Offer for General Maintenance Services for Real Property Safety and Security (RPSS) Gulf Region New Brunswick (NB) Sites
tags: maintenance services request for standing offer Canada Fishery Canada Fisheries Real Property Safety and Security properties
full_summary:
### Request for Standing Offer for General Maintenance Services for Real Property Safety and Security (RPSS) Gulf Region New Brunswick Sites

The Department of Fisheries and Oceans Canada, Real Property Safety and Security Branch, is seeking a Standing Offer for general maintenance services to support the maintenance of its custodial buildings located in New Brunswick, Canada. The general maintenance and repair services will encompass a range of tasks, including structural repairs, electrical maintenance, HVAC system maintenance, plumbing repairs, and miscellaneous labor tasks.

### Objective
The objective of this Standing Offer is to establish a framework for the provision of general maintenance services to support the department's custodial buildings. The services will be provided on an "as-and-when-required" basis to ensure the maintenance and repair of systems, structures, and grounds at DFO sites in the Gulf Region of New Brunswick.

### Background
The Real Property Safety and Security Branch provides essential maintenance services for DFO real property assets. Many of the sites and facilities within the RPSS Gulf Region are operational sites that provide critical services to the Canadian public throughout the year or seasonally. Therefore, it is essential to have a reliable and professional maintenance support system in place to ensure continuous operation of these sites.

### Scope of Work
The general maintenance and repair services to be provided under this Standing Offer will include, but are not limited to:

* Structural repairs, inspections, and maintenance (e.g., interior and exterior carpentry, painting, floor maintenance, and roofing)
* Electrical maintenance and repairs (e.g., component replacement, trouble-shooting, voltage and amperage measurement, and phase rotation testing)
* HVAC system maintenance and repairs (e.g., component replacement, trouble-shooting, cleaning, and inspection of heat pumps, air-handling units, and other related mechanical equipment)
* Civil works (e.g., asphalt repair, ditching, bush-hogging, drainage control, and aggregate application)
* Plumbing maintenance and repairs (e.g., water supply equipment repair, backflow prevention inspections, interior and exterior plumbing fixture repair and replacement)
* Miscellaneous labor tasks to support the maintenance of the above-mentioned tasks

### Trade Agreements
This Standing Offer is subject to the Canada-Chile Free Trade Agreement (CCFTA), Canada-Colombia Free Trade Agreement, Canada-Peru Free Trade Agreement (CPFTA), World Trade Organization Agreement on Government Procurement (WTO GPA), Canada-Panama Free Trade Agreement, Canada-Korea Free Trade Agreement (CKFTA), Canada-Ukraine Free Trade Agreement (CUFTA), Canada-European
